This paper proposes a new algorithmic approach to achieving fairness in machine learning, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the legal and policy implications of their approach, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-category of cyberlaw (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of discrimination, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cryptography (cs.CR) as well as the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
